In addition, infected camels excrete the virus not only via the respiratory tract, but also via the fecal route, which is also the main route of excretion of bats.
We cannot rule out the possibility that the pangolin is one of the intermediate animal hosts of SARS-CoV-2.
In addition, the distance between SARS-CoV-2 and RaTG13 is even smaller than that separating the SARS-CoV-2 and SARS-CoV-2-associated beta-CoV from the pangolin.
