The diversity of bat CoVs offers many opportunities for the emergence of new HCoVs.
In this sense, bat CoVs are genetic reserves of HCoVs.
Among the SARS-CoV accessory proteins, ORF8 was considered important in adapting to humans, since SARS-CoV-related bat viruses were isolated, but encoded divergent ORF8 proteins.
